@node wstep
A blanker. What's that? :) An application which activate a specified function(s) 
if user doesn't touch anything for some time. :) In this case we'll see an aquarium 
with a fishes. :)
@endnode
@node pomysl
It'a not a secret I like AmigaOS. I like using it and programming on this OS. The 
greater part of the time with computers, I spent with AmigaOS especially.
It's sad but true Amiga has a serious and protracted problems with lack of software.
Both, big commercial projects and small utilities.

A some time ago I saw this blanker on my friend's PC.  I though to myself "I want it 
on my Amiga!" What's the problem? I took a look on Aminet but there was nothing in 
Sherman - style.
But it is NOT a problem. I am a programmer - gracious me! I will do this myself. :)
The idea was blocked for long time because of the lack of proper graphics. A PC 
version's authors weren't interest on writing an Amiga OS version. But I got a 
permission for a using Sherman- style graphic. I had a few ideas how to get this 
graphic. One of them was a "take" a graphic directly from a PC version.
And Prodigi did it! I have no idea how he did it! But he did!
Thanks to Prodigi's work on graphic, we can see Sherman Lagoon's on Amiga.
@endnode
@node instalacja
Just run supplied Installer-Script and follow the instruction given.
At the end reset your Amiga
@endnode
@node konfiguracja
You can set a number of fishes, time to make Sherman active, violence :) , sound on/off
graphic scalling, a bottom decoration, screen mode,  run on WB screen.
You can set own background colour if you choose "Own screen" options.
You can also define a tasks list. A list of programs which are running, causes 
Sherman won't be activated.
(for example during watching a movies on Amiga).
Gadget "SAVE" saves actual configuration, "TEST" - you can test actual settings without
saving. And "HIDE" button just hides preference window and makes Sherman ready to 
activate. To make a preference window active just run it from Exchange commodity.
There's also available pull down menu with all functions.
@endnode
@node wymagania
68040+ (can run on 020, but...)
OS3.0+
4MB+ (8MB+ for screen1024x768x16 with background)
~3MB free space on your HDD

disc libraries:
datatypes.library 40+ (OS) (datatypes.library z OS3.5/3.9 recommended)
mrqutilities.library 1+ (included)
asl.library 37+ (OS)
reqtools.library (hope you have it)

other:
picture.datatype 40+
AHI
ILBM.datatype (or any other you want)
AGA (cgx/P96 recommended, CGX 4.x more recommended :) )
xenpl.font (included)
colorwheel.gadget (OS)
Bottom, tubes, textures, fishes raphic are included.
Trajectories - included
Screen palette - included
Sounds - included
sherman.catalog - included polish and english version
If you run Sherman on AGA you MUST use FBlit OR install CGX AGA with disabled option
RTGACCELERATION in Sherman tooltypes!
@endnode
@node wolne
...AGA:
AGA goes to museum. GFX card users know it very well.
AGA chips are very slow and... obsolete. You can't run on them a many moving objects in 8 bit with
satisfied speed. Especially fully compatible with AmigaOS on 40/40 in AGA mode.
Sherman is fully written in assembler code and optimized for AmigaOS as much as I could
do that. IMHO is more harder to write an application fully compatible with AGA system. 
I could write it as a lame-code which patch a bitplanes... it could be faster for sure. :) 
But IMHO it is wrong to write an applications incompatible with system.
It's not a secret I saw an AGA chips a looong time ago. At the very first stage a 
Sherman could not run on AGA. And I never planned to do that. But I find out to NOT 
block a code only for GFX. Finally an optimalisation for GFX not excluded using 
Sherman on AGA chips.
...040 and it's slooow?
Well. Nowadays 040 isn't a cutting edge of technology. :) Yes, it's a quite nice CPU 
with simply procedures but 30 MIPS... ehm. It is not enough right now. BTW a PC version
needs a minimum P60 to run. And a P60 is a "little bit" faster than 040, isn't it? :)
...I have a ZorroII GFX and it's sloow too.
ZooroII doesn't fit to push a lot of graphic through this slots. If your GFX has a 
blitter support, Sherman will use it very well.
...Why datatypes?
Datatypes give us a lot more than we thought. Main advantage is a limitless a number 
recognizebale data formats.
They can remapping graphic (that's makes a Sherman run on AGA and od slower CPU's). 
All graphic is in 256 colours. During loading, graphic is remapped to a pixel format 
and bits on actually opened screen.
On programmer side, datatypes guarantee that an application run without any code 
change on almost every system configuration.
...Why AHI?
Because it makes possible to use a SFX cards.
@endnode
@node darmo
Free? Not excatly. :) If you use a Sherman Lagoon just e-mail me. That's all.
@endnode
@node ikona
DONOTWAIT - standard tooltype, concern an applicationt in sys:wbstartup/ drawer
TASKPRI -  determines a Sherman priority in system.
AHIUNIT - AHI UNIT :)
PRELOADGFX - after Sherman running, a fish - graphic will be loaded to memory till you 
change preferences or till quitting Sherman.
RTGACCELERATION - uses a GFX blitter. Tested on  BVision and Voodoo.
If you use it on AGA - DEACTIVATE it.
AHIFREQ = (44100) - determines withs what frequency works Paula DMA. Deactivate it if 
run on PAL mode.
Leave a 44100 value if you run on GFX card or DblPAL.
@endnode
@node problem
If you have any problems to run Sherman properly just run it from Shell with DEBUG1 
DEBUG2 parameters and send reports to me. (Reports given by Enforcer or Mungwall too, 
of course) :)
...Amithlon problems
There can be a problem if you run it on Amithlon with a GFX card that's doesn't support
a GFX blitter.
Fishes can flashes and speed will be a really slow in that case.
Also can be on CGX3 mode. If Sherman can't run when you click on TEST button, try to 
run it from Shell. (I hope i fixed this bug in this update). Unfortunately (?:) I have 
no permanent acces to Amithlon so I have no idea what is going wrong. :)
But for sure a fault is on Amithlon/P96 side :)
On MorphOS/CGX above problems never happened.
@endnode
